OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1779415426
OL,3,CPaul Brand explains which bills could
OL,4,Crise and what to do to keep costs down.
OL,6,FMeanwhile, the Lea Valley Growers
OL,7,FAssociation warns rising costs could
OL,8,Fsoon affect the price and availability
OL,9,Fof food in supermarkets. 20 percent of
OL,10,Ftheir members have already stopped
OL,11,Fgrowing in recent years because of
OL,12,Frising costs.
OL,14,F"Shoppers are likely again to see
OL,15,Fhigher prices, lack of choice, lower
OL,16,Favailability as soon as there's less
OL,17,Fproduce in the market, then the price
OL,18,Fwill go up."- Lee Stiles, Lea Valley
OL,19,FGrowers Association
OL,26,@vD@AOUzD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1779415426
OL,3,CPaul Brand explains which bills could
OL,4,Crise and what to do to keep costs down.
OL,6,FThe National Farmers' Union says
OL,7,Frising costs and supply chain issues
OL,8,Fcould force some farmers to delay
OL,9,Fplanting next year's crops, or abandon
OL,10,Fthem altogether.
OL,12,FThe Department for Environment, Food
OL,13,Fand Rural affairs says it is "actively
OL,14,Fmonitoring developments in the Middle
OL,15,FEast, and the impacts on the food and
OL,16,Ffarming sector", and says while there
OL,17,Fare "concerns around planting impacts
OL,18,Ffor next year", it "stands ready to
OL,19,Fact swiftly to support our domestic
OL,20,Ffarming industry".
OL,26,@uD@^OUxD@OO]yD@EOUzD@NO]zD@TO]|D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
