OL,3,CPaul Brand explains which bills could
OL,4,Crise and what to do to keep costs down.
OL,6,FWe put these concerns to the
OL,7,FGovernment, and the Treasury told us
OL,8,Fit has "the right economic plan to
OL,9,Fdeal with price rises caused by the
OL,10,Fwar in the Middle East" and is
OL,11,F"supporting families with the cost of
OL,12,Fliving in a responsible way". It says
OL,13,Fthat includes: "#117 off household
OL,14,Fenergy bills, freezing rail fares, and
OL,15,Fincreasing the national living wage to
OL,16,Fgive a nine hundred pound boost to
OL,17,Fmillions of workers"
OL,26,@pD@HOUrD@WO]sD@AOUtD@\O]uD@POUyD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
